  "body": "<!--üíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíé\r\n\r\nHellooo! üòÑ \r\n\r\nTo help us tend to your issue faster, please search our currently open issues before submitting a new one.\r\nExisting issues often contain information about workarounds, resolution, or progress updates.\r\n\r\nüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíé-->\r\n\r\n# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nThere is an improbable race condition between the powchain and proposer service. From the proposer perspective [BlockByTimestamp](https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/develop/beacon-chain/powchain/block_reader.go#L117) reads more than one entry from the latestEth1Header without making a copy or locking the structure.\r\n\r\n        latestBlkHeight := s.latestEth1Data.BlockHeight\r\n\tlatestBlkTime := s.latestEth1Data.BlockTime\r\n\r\n\r\nWhile the powchain service also writes to this structure in another routine without a lock [here](https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/develop/beacon-chain/powchain/service.go#L638).\r\n\r\n\ts.latestEth1Data.BlockHeight = header.Number.Uint64()\r\n\ts.latestEth1Data.BlockHash = header.Hash().Bytes()\r\n\ts.latestEth1Data.BlockTime = header.Time\r\n\r\n\r\nIn an improbable case we could have latestBlkHeight and latestBlkTime referring to two different blocks.\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\nUnsure\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\nN/A. Conceptual Issue.\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\n<pre><code>\r\nN/A\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n**Operating System:**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\nlinux x86_64\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\nkiln\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Anything else relevant (validator index / public key)?**\r\n\r\n",
