    "body": "Thanks for the report here, it is a definitely probably although unlikely edge case. The reason we don't have a lock when writing to it is because everything in our `powchain` service runs on a single event loop, so no multithreaded access is possible there. However `BlockByTimeStamp` is used by external services and the method can be called at anytime. The appropriate thing to do would be to lock it here.",
